article.headline: Dartmouth 96, Plymouth State 47
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Robby Pride came off the bench and scored a game-high 14 points as Dartmouth rolled past Plymouth State, 96-47, on Sunday. Alex Barnett added 12 points, Jabari Trotter had 11, while Kurt Graeber and Ronnie Dixon each chipped in 10 to help Dartmouth (2-5) record its largest margin of victory since Jan 21, 1991, when it defeated Clark University by 50. Bryan Tracy was the only Plymouth State player in double figures with 10 points. Tom Dowd added 7. Plymouth State struggled against the taller Dartmouth squad, hitting just 29.8 percent (17-of-57). The Big Green grabbed 46 rebounds, compared to just 21 for the Panthers. Dartmouth also outscored Plymouth State in the paint by a 50-20 margin. Dartmouth led 46-22 at halftime. The Big Green did not let up later in the game, starting with a 16-4 run to push the lead to 36 points and secure the victory.
